15:53.592 --> 15:59.400
Did you command your men, or how did you motivate 
them to fight?

16:02.604 --> 16:05.228
Well, I obviously commanded them. As in, how did 
you command and motivate them to fight? First of

16:09.033 --> 16:09.874
all, I... I sat high standards. I maintained those 
standards. When I took over the company, I felt it

16:15.667 --> 16:19.414
was a drag tag outfit. They had long hair. They had 
not shaven in days, maybe a week.

16:28.110 --> 16:31.075
The previous company commander had allowed these 
conditions to exist. I felt their morale was down.

16:35.639 --> 16:37.721
I went in there and raised the standards. I said, 
when you're not in contact with the enemy, we will

16:37.842 --> 16:46.832
shave every day.

16:46.872 --> 16:48.113
We got haircuts. We had flippers sent out to us so 
that whenever we weren't fighting, we could get

16:48.234 --> 16:57.064
haircuts and maintain our hygiene. It didn't take 
long for the troops to realize that I was taken care

16:57.084 --> 17:03.351
of. And whenever you're doing down, they'll fight 
for you. But by maintaining standards and

17:10.448 --> 17:17.495
enforcing them, that required them to execute. 
When you require people to execute, they'll fight

17:17.515 --> 17:22.040
for you in combat. Bringing in better food to take

17:22.060 --> 17:27.787
care of. Any time we were on the move or I had people 
out operating independently, I would honor them.

17:34.550 --> 17:41.201
They contact with them constantly by radio, 
asking them where they were. Usually, let's say I

17:42.042 --> 17:50.215
was moving my rifle company five miles in the 
jungle. I'm the guy steering the train, so to

17:52.599 --> 17:56.586
speak. Everyone else tunes out. He's in charge, 
you don't have to worry about him anymore. We might

18:02.950 --> 18:12.994
be strung out over three miles, and I would radio 
back to the plume commanders periodically and ask

18:02.950 --> 18:12.994
them where they were. I kept the pressure on them so 
that they would have to keep up with where they

18:13.784 --> 18:18.128
were. They might be a half mile or a mile behind me, 
but if something happened to me, I was knocked out,

18:18.148 --> 18:25.775
one of them would have to take over. They would have 
to call in the artillery and aircraft. They had to

18:28.778 --> 18:31.341
know where they were to do that. And that was part of 
the training program that I went through. So that

18:35.164 --> 18:39.869
they would know where they were.

18:39.889 --> 18:42.171
Was this motivational? or the level of motivation 
that they felt, is it any different or any lower or

18:43.552 --> 18:54.608
higher than that of an individual coming out of, 
say, boot camp?

19:00.297 --> 19:11.854
I'm not sure there's any

19:00.297 --> 19:11.854
