19:24.065 --> 19:31.493
knowing that you survived. And that's a different 
type of, that's a relief as opposed to a

19:31.513 --> 19:38.039
motivation. After an engagement or a battle, I can 
assure you that everyone was on the emotional

19:43.728 --> 19:46.271
high. I won't call it motivation, but the 
adrenaline would be up and let's say your battle

19:46.351 --> 19:58.643
ended at 5 o'clock in the afternoon. You may stay 
awake all night being unable to sleep or may not be

19:58.663 --> 20:11.856
able to go to sleep until 3 or 4 in the morning 
because of the emotional high that you

19:58.663 --> 20:11.856
experienced after the battle. Was the level of 
motivation or the way in which you commanded your

20:13.951 --> 20:22.619
men any different from the way you led them in 1963?

20:29.745 --> 20:40.415
Well, the situation was entirely different in 68 
and 69 than it was in

20:29.745 --> 20:40.415
63. We didn't have the same problems we were 
engaged in. combat or the threat of engaging with

20:43.229 --> 20:50.455
the enemy did not exist in 1963. So I would say, yes, 
there was a difference. And as a captain in 68 and

20:54.679 --> 21:02.486
69, I was more experienced, more seasoned. You had 
to handle people better. I had a bigger bag of tools

21:03.166 --> 21:11.634
to use

21:03.166 --> 21:11.634
in 1968 than I did in 1963. Sir? Were there any 
problems with sexual harassment of the

21:12.794 --> 21:19.044
Vietnamese or the torching of villages?

21:23.932 --> 21:28.760
