would be lucky to go there. Except some people had 
to get in the Marines, where to get away from the bad

28:45.200 --> 28:50.385
way of life, where they were brought up.

28:53.568 --> 28:59.113
And I actually, I had Marines under me who just 
thrived on being in combat. I had others that did

28:59.133 --> 29:04.237
not. You had stated in your previous interview 
that there's, You didn't really know of any

29:08.433 --> 29:10.716
problems with fragging. You had heard of 
incidences. But was there a level of instruction

29:12.780 --> 29:32.770
or a low level of instruction that the lieutenants 
did not receive or did receive before they went

29:12.780 --> 29:32.770
into Vietnam?

29:32.790 --> 29:34.252
About fragging? Well, no, not about fragging. 
somewhat like about leading and having their men

29:36.074 --> 29:42.281
follow them and not having enough experience.

29:47.867 --> 29:56.617
Well, in the Marine Corps, we send all of our junior 
officers to basic schools where they're trained

29:47.867 --> 29:56.617
as infantrymen. Then they're sent into their 
various schools for their various specialties.

30:03.946 --> 30:05.828
That was a six-month-long school. the top second 
lieutenants, the basics of the Marine Corps, from

30:06.297 --> 30:22.176
maintaining a vehicle to the supply system to 
leadership, many hours of leadership and

30:06.297 --> 30:22.176
tactics.

30:22.637 --> 30:34.572
So yes, the young leaders or the young officers in 
the Marine Corps were prepared before they went in

30:22.637 --> 30:34.572
there. You still have people that aren't the best 
leaders, but get thrown into a situation where

30:36.065 --> 30:47.799
they don't lead well,

30:36.065 --> 30:47.799
and they could get cracked in a case like that. A guy 
that was a typical chicken and uncomfortable with

30:48.460 --> 30:58.512
the troops for some reason could get cracked.

31:03.740 --> 31:07.444
possibly even staff not commissioned officers 
could be, I don't know. The fragging that I heard

31:07.464 --> 31:21.300
about was always back in the rear area, a base camp, 
so to speak, where you had a large transit

31:07.464 --> 31:21.300
population going in and out. These were people 
that were avoiding going out into the combat

31:21.320 --> 31:28.328
units. They were the recalcitrants.

31:35.127 --> 31:38.091
I don't guess they might have retaliated. I have no 
friends and no one by name that was fractured.

31:48.327 --> 31:51.732
You're talking about the staff positions.

31:54.616 --> 32:04.611
What was the general feeling towards the rear 
echelon people, being that they had never seen the

32:04.895 --> 32:05.976
front line?

32:13.786 --> 32:23.157
Well, I don't know how to answer that, mainly 
because I didn't have any feelings one way or the

32:13.786 --> 32:23.157
other about it. I had my job to do, and I was out there 
doing it. The people in the rear had to provide the

32:30.545 --> 32:34.690
support for me and the intelligence. So they were 
providing a vital function for me.

32:47.467 --> 32:51.392
Turn that off

32:47.467 --> 32:51.392
just a second. There was the standard joke around 
about the USO shows like Bob Hope and the others and

32:51.412 --> 32:58.341
Margaret and so forth. that would come into 
Vietnam. It was always the guys in the rear that got

33:00.321 --> 33:07.530
to go to those shows, and never the guys in the 
field. The guys up winning the war never got to

33:07.550 --> 33:16.221
enjoy St. Bob Hope and Aunt Margaret or something 
like that. And so in that regard, there was

33:16.241 --> 33:21.588
resentment for the folks in the field. I pertain 
to, let's say, big decision-making, when a big

33:29.067 --> 33:36.415
operation is going to happen and a general officer 
makes a decision, the general officer is not

33:29.067 --> 33:36.415
fighting on the front line. How is that felt by many 
of the people on the front line when they had to

33:37.356 --> 33:50.111
follow somebody who didn't really, or in their 
mind, they didn't feel that he knew the situation,

33:37.356 --> 33:50.111
what was going on in the front line? I'm not sure 
that anyone even thought like that until I didn't

33:50.131 --> 33:55.817
know what the situation was. We all hoped that the 
general knew what he was doing, and that any

33:58.649 --> 34:20.842
mission that we were sent on was a valid mission, 
because there was always the possibility that you

33:58.649 --> 34:20.842
would lose someone, and you didn't want to lose 
someone for a mission that was executed

33:58.649 --> 34:20.842
on time. Yes, sir. What was the general consensus 
pertaining to the way people demonstrated back in

34:21.063 --> 34:27.913
the United States against the war?

34:30.813 --> 34:35.857
Well, I don't think you can say there's a general 
consensus. If you were a liberal, you would say

34:35.877 --> 34:40.522
that the demonstrations were good and you were all 
for them. If you were a conservative, you would say

34:40.542 --> 34:45.826
that the demonstrations were bad. Was there a poll 
taken by the media? I'm sure there was with George

34:51.331 --> 34:59.318
Harris and everyone else, and they could say so 
many, a certain percentage was for the war and a

34:51.331 --> 34:59.318
certain percentage was not. I don't recall any of 
the numbers now, but I'm sure that the majority of

35:00.158 --> 35:10.032
the people supported the war effort initially. 
And as the war dragged on, and I mean month by month,

35:10.052 --> 35:14.979
that supported the time. And at some point, I'm 
sure it was less than 50% of the nation. I know that

35:19.905 --> 35:21.588
supported the war. I know whenever ICAF came home 
from Vietnam in 1969, the general reaction,

35:27.715 --> 35:30.679
people in my home from the people in my hometown. 
Well, I guess the war is necessary. You guys are

35:34.104 --> 35:39.391
there for a good cause, but I just wish the war would 
be over. The Americans are the nature of the

35:39.411 --> 35:46.782
Americans is we like to get in and do something 
quickly. Be done with it, whether it's in business

35:46.802 --> 35:51.208
or anything else. And I think that was the general 
attitude toward war. Let's get in and get this

35:55.644 --> 36:00.969
thing over with so we can put it behind us. Were 
there specific liberal or conservative

36:00.989 --> 36:16.043
separations in the field, like groups of 
individuals who did believe in one way and groups

36:00.989 --> 36:16.043
that believed in another way for the war and 
against the war? Oh, I'm sure there were. I'm sure

36:19.146 --> 36:21.668
there were individuals who believed that way. 
When you're in a rifle company and you're out in the

36:22.053 --> 36:29.843
field, though, everyone's life depends on how 
well the fella next to him does his job. It's called

36:31.085 --> 36:32.046
survival. You don't choose teams, you just decide 
to debate when you're out there in the field,

36:34.289 --> 36:44.682
because that's the wrong time.

36:44.702 --> 36:50.490
When I was in the field the whole time, we were back 
in the rear area, club, drinking a few beers. I'm

36:51.517 --> 36:56.223
sure they've got decent debates like that. But we 
had a job to do. As I say, our survival depended on

36:58.386 --> 37:03.554
everyone doing their job. Were there many racial 
problems between whites, blacks, and Vietnamese

37:03.574 --> 37:09.382
in the field? Well, again, we didn't operate with 
the Vietnamese, so I didn't see any racial

37:09.402 --> 37:17.052
problems with the Americans and the Vietnamese.

37:19.900 --> 37:30.376
And out in the field, there were

37:19.900 --> 37:30.376
no racial problems. I would not have tolerated 
him. When I say that, I wouldn't have. He said, what

37:32.839 --> 37:34.061
would I have done? Had I had problems? I don't know. 
But I didn't have any problems. I do know back in the

37:39.770 --> 37:47.241
rear area, the blacks would congregate in one area 
and do their thing.

37:51.136 --> 37:53.058
I just don't have any first-hand experience.

37:56.001 --> 38:06.152
But where everyone's life depends on the fellow 
next to him, and if he's in a combat situation, we

37:56.001 --> 38:06.152
just don't have that problem. I'm talking about 
infantry company, not civil. The guy that you

38:10.617 --> 38:15.802
share a boxhole with, if you're white, may be 
black. And the color of the skin doesn't make any

38:15.822 --> 38:20.367
difference when you're in that situation. I had 
one platoon that was led by a black sergeant, one of

38:20.920 --> 38:39.308
the finest men I know, a tremendous leader, and he 
had no trouble at all running that platoon. When I

38:39.329 --> 38:48.042
was a sergeant running a platoon, I had a shortage 
of staff, non-commissioned officers, and this

38:39.329 --> 38:48.042
platoon leader went back to the United States 
Three weeks leave, and it took him a while to get

38:48.713 --> 39:03.737
back, but this black sergeant ran the platoon for 
about five weeks, and I was lost in responsibility

38:48.713 --> 39:03.737
for a

38:48.713 --> 39:03.737
young man. My weapons platoon commander was a 
black staff sergeant,

39:03.757 --> 39:09.727
and he had no problems. So out in the field, I just 
didn't experience any problems.

